table asyncio_extra198.asyncio_InvalidStateError_identity:
  description: "asyncio.InvalidStateError class identity checks in asyncioexceptions198 namespace — InvalidStateError.__name__=='InvalidStateError' (len=17: I(1)n(2)v(3)a(4)l(5)i(6)d(7)S(8)t(9)a(10)t(11)e(12)E(13)r(14)r(15)o(16)r(17); raised when an operation is performed on a Future in an invalid state, e.g. calling result() on a pending Future); InvalidStateError.__module__=='asyncio.exceptions' (len=18; defined in the pure-Python asyncio.exceptions submodule alongside CancelledError); InvalidStateError.__name__ (17) < InvalidStateError.__module__ (18) by 1 — the name is just one character shorter than the module path; InvalidStateError.__name__ (17) > CancelledError.__name__ (14) by 3; InvalidStateError.__module__ (18) == CancelledError.__module__ (18) — both share the same submodule; verified with Python 3.14.3"
